===Adverb===
{{head|en|adverb|head=[[here]] and [[there]]}}

# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} In, at or to various places; in one place and another.
#*{{quote-book|year=1893|author={{w|Walter Besant}}|title=[http://gutenberg.org/ebooks/34738 The Ivory Gate]|chapter=Prologue
|passage=Thus, when he drew up instructions in lawyer language{{...}}his clerks{{...}}understood him very well. If he had written a love letter, or a farce, or a ''ballade'', or a story, no one, either clerks, or friends, or compositors, would have understood anything but a word '''here and''' a word '''there'''.}}
#* '''1900''', {{w|L. Frank Baum}}, {{w|The Wonderful Wizard of Oz}}
#*: They thanked him and bade him good-bye, and turned toward the West, walking over fields of soft grass dotted '''here and there''' with daisies and buttercups.
#* '''1912''': {{w|Edgar Rice Burroughs}}, {{w|Tarzan of the Apes}}, Chapter 6
#*: '''Here and there''' the brilliant rays penetrated to earth, but for the most part they only served to accentuate the Stygian blackness of the jungle's depths.
# {{context|idiomatic|lang=en}} [[from time to time|From time to time]].

